context: This year, George Brown College theatre programs' graduating students will host live, online performances of The Corsican Complaint in August 2021. The performances will be broadcast via YouTube. Donations are being accepted for the COVID-19 Student Emergency Relief Fund instead of admission fees. The fund supports students at George Brown College who have experienced financial hardships due to the pandemic. Donors will receive a tax receipt for donations of $20 or more. For more information about making a donation or other ways to support, contact Gabriella Goutam at gabriella.goutam@georgebrown.ca or 416-415-5000 ext. 3289. The play-related questions should be directed to Cindy.Bautista@georgebrown.ca. The text also includes contact information for the college, including a phone number and email address, as well as a link to sign up for college news and updates. The information in the website is subject to change without notice.
